Consider the following:<br>
1. This summer, Moammar Ghaddafi almost became the next UN Human Rights Commissioner, succeeding the Irish terror-supporter and Jew-hater Mary Robinson.<br>
2. More than half of all UN resolutions passed in its entire history were resolutions condemning Israel.<br>
3. The UN has not confronted an agressor-state militarily since it intervened against North Korea in 1950 and that only because the Soviet Union was foolishly boycotting the Security Council when the vote came up. The UN permitted the Cambodian genocide of the 1970s, the Rwanda genocide of the 1990s, and the long-running racist slave-war in Sudan. Its hare-brained attempt at &quot;nation-building&quot; in Somalia resulted in something like 10,000 dead Somalis. The excuse was famine. As one Somali said, &quot;we didn't know that the food shipments were just fattening us up for the slaughter.&quot;<br>
More recently, UN forces completely failed to stop a mob of ill-trained bandits from terrorizing the population of Sierra Leone. <br>
4. Far from uniting the world, the UN has presided over the greatest breakup of sovereign multi-national states since the middle ages and the trend is accelerating. Yugoslavia, the  Soviet Union, Ethiopia, Czechoslovakia and Pakistan all broke up into ethnically defined sovereignties. Canada, the United Kingdom, Spain, and any number of other countries are threatened by separatist movements who want to create their own ethnically pure nations. <br>
<br>
Arm these inept totalitarians with nukes, and Israel will go up in flames and ruthless third world dictators will have a license for any atrocity that strikes their fancy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=johnfraz>John Fraz</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_yingyang.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 247<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/23/02 6:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=431.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://lneilsmith.com/tools/littlelogo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Your nightmare, not mine</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&gt;... the Orwellian agenda and authoritarian hypocrisy<br>
so typical of internationalists.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
 You ignored another of my main points:<br>
Democratic, transparent, and accountable to the will of the people. The present UN is none of these.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&gt; The evil nature of unilateral military action is<br>
not implicit in its definition, and it is simply dishonest<br>
and authoritarian to claim that it is.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
 Defining evil as self-centered greed, I'd argue that it most certainly is implicit!<br>
<br>
No time for more now, I'll end with Alexander Hamilton<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://memory.loc.gov/const/fed/fedpapers.html">memory.loc.gov/const/fed/fedpapers.html</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
&quot;Why has government been instituted at all? Because the passions of men will not conform to the dictates of reason &amp; justice without restraint. Has it been found that bodies of men act with more rectitude and greater disinterestedness than individuals? The contrary of this has been inferred by all accurate observers of the conduct of mankind.&quot;<br>
<br>
an excerpt from Federalist Papers, No. 15:<br>
&quot;...   In addition to all this, there is in the nature of sovereign power an impatience of control that disposes those who are invested with the exercise of it to look with an evil eye upon all external attempts to <br>
restrain or direct its operations.<br>
From this spirit it happens that in every political association which is formed upon the principle of uniting in a common interest a number of lesser sovereignties, there will be found a kind of eccentric tendency in the subordinate or inferior orbs by the operation of which there will be a perpetual effort in each to fly off from the common center.<br>
This tendency is not difficult to be accounted for.  It has its origin in the love for power.<br>
Power controlled or abridged is almost always the rival and enemy of that power by which it is controlled or abridged.<br>
This simple proposition will teach us how little reason there is to expect that the persons intrusted with the administration of the affairs of the particular members of a confederacy will at all times be ready with perfect good humor and an unbiased regard to the public weal to execute the resolutions or decrees of the general authority.  The reverse of this results from the constitution of man.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=atomicconspiracy>Atomic Conspiracy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/23/02 8:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=431.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Horse manure</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&gt; The evil nature of unilateral military action is<br>
not implicit in its definition, and it is simply dishonest<br>
and authoritarian to claim that it is.<br>
<br>
Defining evil as self-centered greed, I'd argue that it most certainly is implicit!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Oh, for heaven's sake, this is merely a reiteration of your original pronouncement, essentially saying that it is evil because it is evil. If we define internationalism as organized looting, we can argue that it is a criminal enterprise. So what? This is circular reasoning and assuming the conclusion. <br>
A nation state apparently acts in its own interest; but it is, in itself, a collective entity usually composed of millions of people. Internationalists see this as greed or self-centeredness only by pretending that it is a monolith akin to an individual person. In any case, how would a global super-state be any different? Would its leaders and bureaucrats be magically immune from the automatically evil and nefarious motives of such national leaders as Roosevelt or Churchill? <br>
Demonstrate that an international organization would not have the same evil motives that you ascribe to national governments. If it is truly sovereign, how is it different from a nation-state except in scale? If it is not sovereign, how do you keep the evil/greedy member states from infecting it with their evil and greed, as we see at the UN? <br>
Suppose we do have a worldwide democracy? What keeps the vote-rich but materially poor regions from systematically looting the wealthy ones? With a monopoly on nuclear weapons as the instrument of coercion, this would be easy. This need for a &quot;redistribution of wealth&quot; is what internationalists really mean when they attribute such individual characteristics as greed and selfishness to the collective entities known as nation-states.<br>
Nuclear weapons are potentially a source of absolute power. This can't be done now because more than one set of decision makers have control of them, rendering them useless through their own deterrent effect. Take that away, and the controlling power becomes absolute.<br>
In any case, it's a fantasy. Liberal idealists won't even keep Canada together, or prevent a new nation-state from arising in Scotland. How will they unite the world?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=atomoftenacity>AtomOfTenacity </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Space Tourist</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/23/02 10:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=431.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/user/atom_of_tenacity.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Horse manure</span><hr size=1> First of all, how did this thread get so far off topic? Anyway, I agree with AC and his stance on the subject of international control of nuclear weapons. When it comes to Internationalism vs. Nationalism, the latter has, is and always will be the lesser evil of the two.  <br>
Because there has never been total world governmental control, we don’t have any direct working examples of Internationalism in effect on a global scale that we can observe. However, given that Nationalism can produce ugly results when taken to the extreme (Nazism, Fascism, Imperialism, etc), it pales in comparison to what life (death) would be like under an Internationalist government. Just take any totalitarian state from the last century, but put it into a picture of that regime/s operating on a GLOBAL scale. Now that’s a scary thought indeed.<br>
The major proponents and groups that we face everyday who want to rob us of our freedoms are usually financed by tax exempt foundations, such as the Internationalist foundations set up by the Rockefellers and other One-Worlders. These groups (and this is esp. true of “Green” groups and anti-nukers) work and strive towards building up the UN, whether they are aware of it or not.<br>
Anyone who does a little research can easily see that the UN has and is going to be the vehicle through which the Internationalists will achieve world government.<br>
However, most important is to come to the realization of what the “menace” of nuclear weapons has actually brought upon the U.S. and the world as a whole. It is the often times played up threat of nuclear destruction that has been used over and over and over again to help in fomenting emotions in people for world government. Real or imaged, the threat of nuclear destruction has been pounded day and night into the psyche of almost every living adult the world over via movies, leaders, propaganda, etc. The results have been sovereignty-stripping treaties (most often in favor of the Reds too) brainwashing of the youth in rejecting nuclear power for peaceful reasons but most importantly the transfer of power to the UN, which I do not have time to discuss in detail.    <br>
The end product is a clamoring for the growth and empowerment of the UN, which is precisely what the Internationalists have wanted all along.<br>
Lets not fall into the same trap by advocating International (UN) control of nuclear weapons.  <br>
