e any problems from protesters and the like finding you, and even if they did find you there wouldn't be much they could do unless they had depth charges (defending yourself from hostile divers would be like shooting goldfish in a barrel.)  I was also reading lately that it might be possible to extract molecules of uranium from sea water itself so you might not even have to import your nuclear fuel if such an extraction technology could be created. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=discovery1@nuclearspace>Discovery 1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 127<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/28/02 6:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=431.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: The Greatest Generation</span><hr size=1> Building an Orion research facility under water would be quite an achievement, perhaps as great as building an Orion.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=discovery1@nuclearspace>Discovery 1</A> at: 10/28/02 6:50:30 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2357<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/28/02 8:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=431.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The Greatest Generation</span><hr size=1> Depends on the depth. International waters are mostly very deep but there are spots where 'Islands' don't quite meet the surface. Any cavern systems found there could have water pumped out and then sealed.<br>
An alternative might be to simply use caverns above sea level. An option I've been researching the past couple of weeks. Limestone caves are the most common and extremely hardy fortresses quite capable of surviving nuclear bombardment. The fossil limestone absorbs shockwaves rather than shattering. The deepest cave systems have yet to be discovered and practically every mountainous region has them.<br>
<br>
Glaciers do move. Very slowly. They also melt to water on contact with heat, water which can be pumped away or used for drinking. Continents also drift, although at a much slower rate. The foundations under the Glacier is steadfast enough and with nuclear power we can shape and size the configuration of the base to any dimensions we please. Under kilometres of ice, nobody will be able to detect any change to the environment. The only possible danger is the roof falling down. Heavily compacted ice shouldn't disintegrate. Heat rising will melt the ice to a certain height then it will stop raining quite so hard. I think it would be safe. Igloo's rarely fall on Eskimo's because they have a small fire inside. We'd need professional advice from civil engineers on the project. Worst case scenario, we have to build a dome to support the roof I'm guessing.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=discovery1@nuclearspace>Discovery 1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 129<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/28/02 10:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=431.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/7.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: The Greatest Generation</span><hr size=1> I don't know. Even if we did build it in shallow water, it would still be difficult. There is an underwater hotel in southern Florida. That would probably give some insight into how much it would cost to build an Orion reacher facility under water.<br>
<br>
The limestone caves seem to be a good idea, but it would cost a fortune to retrofit them. Also, what happens when you reach a particularly narrow point in the cave? You could use explosives to widen it, surely, but that might trigger a collapse. Then again, I don't know that much about how limestone would react to such treatment. <br>
<br>
But then again, maybe we are going about this all wrong. If we are merely solving the technical problems of an Orion, like the shock absorbers, we can simply conduct our reach where the climate is less than favorable for protestors, like Siberia. Building an Orion is a completely different matter, however.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=431.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=431.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=431.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=431.topic&index=38><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=431.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.threadControl?topicID=431.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=431.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=431.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.